headline: The Industrial REIT Prologis Is a Data Center Play. Why Some Analysts Don’t See It as a Buy.
summary: On the conference call, analysts mostly wanted to know about its side-venture in artificial intelligence data centers.  For a year, Prologis has been talking about data centers as an opportunity adjacent to the 6,000 logistics centers it has around the world.  There’s room for data centers that would consume 10 gigawatts of power, the company says.

headline: Plymouth Industrial Announces Acquisition Approval by Stockholders
summary: PLYM stockholders approve a $2.1B all-cash buyout by Makarora and Ares, paving the way for a Jan. 27 close and taking the REIT private.
